            <title type="main">
              <hi rend="i">COLERIDGE SUMMER CONFERENCE</hi>
            </title>
          </head>
          <p>The Friends of Coleridge in Somerset will be holding the first Coleridge Summer Conference from
25 to 28 July 1988, in Nether Stowey, Somerset, England. This is the first conference held in this region,
within one hundred yards of Coleridge Cottage, and at the center of the Quantock countryside which influenced
the major poetry of Coleridge and the early writing of Wordsworth. The main speakers will include Coleridge
scholars Jack Stillinger, K. M. Wheeler, and Peter Larkin, and the distinguished local historian Robert
Dunning. If you wish to submit a proposal for a conference session or a paper on Coleridge or related areas of
the romantic movement please contact Dr. David S. Miall, Coleridge Summer Conference 1988, The College of St.
Paul &amp; St. Mary, The Park, Cheltenham, GL50 2RH, England. For further information contact Mrs. Rosemary
Cawthray, Coleridge Cottage, 35 Lime Street, Nether Stowey, Bridgwater, TA5 1NQ, England.</p>
